org.apache.hadoop.registry.client.impl.zk

接口 ZookeeperConfigOptions

  • 所有已知实现类:
    MicroZookeeperService

    public interface ZookeeperConfigOptions
    Configuration options which are internal to Zookeeper, as well as some other ZK constants

    Zookeeper options are passed via system properties prior to the ZK Methods/classes being invoked. This implies that:

    1. There can only be one instance of a ZK client or service class in a single JVM —else their configuration options will conflict.
    2. It is safest to set these properties immediately before invoking ZK operations.

    • 字段详细资料

      • PROP_ZK_ENABLE_SASL_CLIENT

        static final String PROP_ZK_ENABLE_SASL_CLIENT
        Enable SASL secure clients: "zookeeper.sasl.client". This is usually set to true, with ZK set to fall back to non-SASL authentication if the SASL auth fails by the property PROP_ZK_SERVER_MAINTAIN_CONNECTION_DESPITE_SASL_FAILURE.

        As a result, clients will default to attempting SASL-authentication, but revert to classic authentication/anonymous access on failure.

        System property for the JAAS client context : "zookeeper.sasl.clientconfig". For SASL authentication to work, this must point to a context within the

        Default value is derived from ZooKeeperSaslClient.LOGIN_CONTEXT_NAME_KEY

        static final String PROP_ZK_SASL_CLIENT_USERNAME
        The SASL client username: "zookeeper.sasl.client.username".

        Set this to the short name of the client, e.g, "user", not user/host, or user/host@REALM
